Matrix A is as follows:

A = [3  2  1;
      2  1  2;
      1  2  3]

However, the team coach decided to change the performance metrics. Now, the first column is the number of assists, the second column is the number of saves, and the third column is the number of goals scored. This change in metrics can be represented by a permutation matrix, P:

P = [0  0  1;
      1  0  0;
      0  1  0]

Given that the new performance matrix (B) can be obtained by the multiplication of A and P (B = AP), find matrix B. Then, determine the inverse of matrix B, if it exists. If the inverse doesn't exist, explain why.
